  "prompt": "Why do people get depressed when they're unemployed?",
  "response": "People can get depressed when unemployed for several reasons:\n\n1. Financial stress\n- Difficulty paying bills\n- Worry about basic survival needs\n- Anxiety about future financial stability\n\n2. Loss of identity and self-worth\n- Work often provides a sense of purpose\n- Professional identity becomes threatened\n- Feeling of being unproductive or useless\n\n3. Social isolation\n- Less daily social interaction\n- Reduced opportunities to connect with others\n- Potential withdrawal from social circles\n\n4. Reduced structure and routine\n- Lack of daily schedule\n- Decreased sense of accomplishment\n- Potential loss of motivation\n\n5. Psychological impact\n- Feelings of failure\n- Lowered self-esteem\n- Uncertainty about future prospects\n\n6. Perceived loss of control\n- Limited ability to influence job market\n- Feeling powerless about career trajectory\n\n7. Comparison with peers\n- Feeling behind in professional development\n- Social pressure to be employed\n- Potential stigma of unemployment\n\n8. Disrupted personal and professional goals\n- Interrupted career progression\n- Delayed personal milestones\n- Potential long-term career setbacks\n\nThese factors can interact and compound, leading to increased risk of depression during unemployment.",
